Copyright (c) 2026 Digital Syria Vision contributors.

This repository contains a strategic proposal, supporting documentation, and a
non-functional prototype for a national digital transformation programme. It is
published for planning, evaluation, and discussion purposes only.

Permission is hereby granted, free of charge, to any person or government body
obtaining a copy of this material to:

  1. Read, share, and adapt the documents and prototype code for the purposes
     of planning, evaluating, or implementing a national digital transformation
     programme, with appropriate attribution.

  2. Reproduce excerpts of the documents in policy briefs, ministerial papers,
     academic work, and donor proposals, with attribution to "Digital Syria
     Vision" and a link to the source repository.

  3. Modify, extend, and re-distribute the prototype code under the terms of
     the MIT License (full text below).

The following are NOT permitted:

  - Presenting this material as an official policy of the Syrian government,
    the Ministry of Communications, or any other public body, unless such an
    endorsement has been granted in writing.

  - Removing the prototype/mock-data disclaimers from any redistributed copy
    of the prototype.

  - Citing the financial or KPI numbers in this repository as committed
    targets. They are planning scenarios, not commitments.

